                                <tr>
                                  <td colspan="3" align="center" valign="top" class="titel"><h2>How to Place an Order of Custom Jeans</h2></td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                  <td height="20" colspan="3" align="left" valign="top" class="font10"><img src="images/5.gif" width="13" height="13" style=" padding-top:2px" /><strong> Select the fabric &amp; styles</strong></td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                  <td colspan="3" align="left" valign="top" ><div align="justify">
                                    <ul>
                                      <li class="font10"><strong>Fabric</strong> - Select the Fabric from  our large collection of Denim Fabric Samples. (This will select the fabric  quality &amp; the primary enzyme wash treatment).<br />
                                      </li>
                                      <li class="font10" style="padding-top:10px;"><strong>Special Wash</strong> - Select the special wash treatment  if you want your jeans look stylish.</li>
                                      <li class="font10" style="padding-top:10px;"><strong>Thread Color</strong> - Select the thread color  you want. You can select secondary thread color also, which can be used at  certain stitches. Also, you can specify where you want to use the secondary  thread under special note at the end of measurements.</li>
                                      <li class="font10" style="padding-top:10px;"><strong>Pocket Style</strong> - Select the front pocket  &amp; back pocket style. If you want your own styled front &amp; back pocket, select  my own design &amp; send us the photo of the pocket style you want. If you are  going with our default pocket style, we will make your jeans with basic  5-pocket pattern, which is universal style for jeans in all countries in the  world.</li>
                                      <li class="font10" style="padding-top:10px;"><strong>Fly Style</strong> - Select the fly style you  want, the Zip Fly or the Button Fly.</li>
                                    </ul>
                                  </div></td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                  <td colspan="3" align="left" valign="top" class="font10"><div align="justify"><strong><img src="images/5.gif" width="13" height="13" style=" padding-top:2px" /> Measurements</strong>
                                      <ul>
                                      <li>Select one option from "Make My Jeans" &amp; "Copy A Jeans"<strong></strong></li>
                                      <ul>
                                        <li><strong>Make My Jeans</strong> - First Select fitting type  according to what type of fitting you want for your jeans. Give your exact body  measurements as described &amp; shown in the photographs. We will leave extra  loosing as described in "Fitting Guide Table". So refer table first &amp; then  decide your fitting type.</li>
                                        <li><strong>Copy A Jeans</strong> - If you already have a  perfect jeans and you like it the most, then you can send us all the measurements  to us by following the instructions in "Copy A Jeans" section. We will make the  perfect copy of your favorite jeans. Please note we can copy only the  measurements, not the fabric and accessories.</li>
                                      </ul>
                                      <li>The measurements written in the measurement box by you will be the  final measurements for your order processing. To change or modify it, contact  us by E-mail or by phone and we will inform you about your order status and we  will tell you what modification can we able to do at that stage.</li>
                                    </ul>
                                  </div></td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                  <td colspan="3" align="left" valign="top" class="font10"><div align="justify"><strong><img src="images/5.gif" width="13" height="13" style=" padding-top:2px" /> Conform Your  Order</strong>
                                      <ul>
                                      <li>By pressing  PROCEED tab; you will be redirected to "Conform Order" page. On conform order  page, you will see all the details you selected during order, you can again  modify order by clicking edit tab.</li>
                                      <li>After conform  yourself by reading all about your order, press PROCEED tab.</li>
                                    </ul>
                                  </div></td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                  <td height="25" colspan="3" align="left" valign="middle" class="font10"><strong><img src="images/5.gif" width="13" height="13" style=" padding-top:2px" /></strong><strong> Make  Payment.</strong></td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                  <td width="25" align="left" valign="top" class="font10">&nbsp;</td>
                                  <td width="1261" colspan="2" align="left" valign="top" class="font10">You can make payments by different ways. We  provide PayPal (direct pay by Paypal &amp; by your credit card), net-banking,  cheque or cash deposit and send a demand draft options.</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                  <td colspan="3" align="left" valign="top" class="font10"><strong><img src="images/5.gif" width="13" height="13" style=" padding-top:2px" /></strong><strong> Delivery</strong></td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                  <td align="left" valign="top" class="font10"><strong><br />
                                  </strong></td>
                                  <td colspan="2" align="left" valign="top" class="font10">After conform your payment, we will start the jeans  making process for you, and we will dispatch your jeans within 30 days after  conformation of your payment. After dispatching from here, it will take 3-5  days to deliver in India and 6-9 days to deliver out of India.</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                  <td colspan="3" align="left" valign="top" class="font10"><strong><img src="images/5.gif" width="13" height="13" style=" padding-top:2px" /></strong><strong> Enjoy  wearing SQ Jeans.</strong></td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                  <td height="20" align="left" valign="top" class="font10">&nbsp;</td>
                                  <td colspan="2" align="left" valign="top" class="font10">The SQ Jeans come ready to wear &amp;  pre-shrunk. Wear it &amp; enjoy</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                  <td height="38" align="left" valign="top" class="titel_1">&nbsp;</td>
                                  <td align="center"><img src="images/sequeiralogo.jpg" width="600" height="80" /></td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                  <td align="left" valign="top" class="titel_1">&nbsp;</td>
                                  <td colspan="2" align="center" valign="top" ><h2><strong>Measurements guidelines</strong></h2></td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                  <td align="justify" valign="top" class="font10">&nbsp;</td>
                                  <td colspan="2" align="justify" valign="top" class="font10">Select one option from &quot;Make My Jeans&quot; or &quot;Copy A Jeans&quot;</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                  <td colspan="3" align="justify" valign="top" class="font10"><ul>
                                    <li><strong class="red_font10">Make My Jeans</strong> - First select a fitting  type. Select fitting type according to what type of fitting you want for your  jeans. We will leave loosing at the parts of seat, thighs and knee as shown in  the "Fitting Guide Table". Choose one option from five as per your requirements.<br />
                                      <ul>
                                        <li><strong>Super Skinny</strong> - Super tight fitting jeans with narrow bottom. This option is  especially for women who like to wear perfect super skin tight jeans. You should  select this option if you have chosen any full stretchable denim fabric. <img src="images/home pic.jpg" alt="custom made jeans" width="350" height="290" style="float:right;margin-left:10px;margin-bottom:5px" />You can also choose broad bottom to make your jeans boot cut. Upper fitting above  knee remains same with narrow or boot-cut bottom.</li>
                                        <li><strong>Skinny</strong> - Tight fitting jeans with narrow bottom. This option is  especially for women who like to wear perfect super skin tight jeans. You should  select this option if you have chosen any full stretchable denim fabric. You can also choose broad bottom to make your jeans boot cut. Upper fitting above  knee remains same with narrow or boot-cut bottom.</li>
                                        <li><strong>Slim</strong> - Fitting jeans with narrow bottom, but not as tight as super skinny or skinny jeans. Women &amp; Men both can use this option. You can also choose broad  bottom to make your jeans boot cut. Upper fitting above knee remains same with  narrow or boot-cut bottom.</li>
                                        <li><strong>Straight </strong>- Not much tight &amp; not much loose, looks slim but feels  comfortable. Widely used in young generation. You can also choose broad bottom  to make your jeans boot cut. Upper fitting above knee remains same with narrow  or boot-cut bottom.</li>
                                        <li><strong>Comfort</strong> - Slightly tapered at bottom part &amp; free at thighs part.  Feel most comfort with non-stretchable denims too. Do not go for boot cut shape  when choose comfort fitting type.</li>
                                        <li><strong>Baggy</strong> - For those, who do not like tight jeans. This fitting type will  be extreme loose at thighs and knee, you can choose bottom measure of your  choice. Do not go for boot cut shape when choose baggy fitting type.<br />
                                          <br />
                                        </li>
                                      </ul>
                                    </li>
                                    <li><strong class="red_font10">Copy A Jeans</strong>
                                      <ul>
                                        <li>If you already have a perfect jeans and you like it the most, then you  can send us all the measurements by following the instructions in "Copy A  Jeans" section. We will make the perfect copy of your favorite jeans.</li>
                                        <li>You can send us your favorite jeans for measurements to our address at  your cost, and we will send a copy of that jeans with a new one of our brand SQ  Jeans along with your favorite jeans.(  kindly note - As our jeans are handmade there can be some discrepancy in some  measurements &amp; the grip of the jeans vary from fabric to fabric, nothing  can be exact duplicate). And, please note we can copy only the measurements, not the fabric and  accessories.</li>
                                      </ul>
                                    </li>
                                  </ul>                                    </td>
                                </tr>
